From 02d4fc7fc00850b2d135e4cdba85388182cdb0a1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sean Smith <DefendTheDisabled@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 9 Apr 2026 16:00:24 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 09/16] ntfs3: map ptime to NTFS Date Created in
 getattr/setattr

Maps ptime to NTFS Date Created (birth time / i_crtime on Linux)
for ntfs3 getattr/setattr operations. This is the "mapped" ptime
architecture: on cross-platform filesystems (NTFS, FAT, exFAT)
that already have a settable creation time in Windows, ptime
writes overwrite the creation time directly.

Rationale: NTFS creation time is natively mutable via Windows
APIs (SetFileTime) and standard tools. Linux should at minimum
match this behavior. The forensic argument against settable
btime applies only to Linux-native filesystems (btrfs, ext4)
where btime has always been append-only.

Implementation touches:
- ntfs3 getattr (fs/ntfs3/file.c): copy i_crtime to kstat.ptime
  when STATX_PTIME requested. Always reports (no zero check)
  because NTFS creation time is always set.
- ntfs3 setattr (fs/ntfs3/file.c): handle ATTR_PTIME by writing
  attr->ia_ptime to inode->i_crtime, marking the inode dirty.
- ntfs_save_frecord (fs/ntfs3/frecord.c): persist i_crtime to
  the on-disk STANDARD_INFORMATION attribute in NTFS record
  format (kernel_to_nt_time conversion).

Rename preservation is handled in a separate commit.

Ref: Decision #49 (mapped ptime architecture for NTFS/FAT/exFAT)
Ref: Decision #44 (5-FS scope including ntfs3)
Files: fs/ntfs3/file.c (ntfs3 getattr, ntfs3 setattr)
Files: fs/ntfs3/frecord.c (ntfs_save_frecord)
---
 fs/ntfs3/file.c    | 13 +++++++++++++
 fs/ntfs3/frecord.c |  8 ++++++++
 2 files changed, 21 insertions(+)

diff --git a/fs/ntfs3/file.c b/fs/ntfs3/file.c
index 13d014b878f6..8688a48b1c81 100644
--- a/fs/ntfs3/file.c
+++ b/fs/ntfs3/file.c
@@ -161,6 +161,13 @@ int ntfs_getattr(struct mnt_idmap *idmap, const struct path *path,
 
 	stat->result_mask |= STATX_BTIME;
 	stat->btime = ni->i_crtime;
+
+	/* Map NTFS creation time to ptime (provenance time) */
+	if (request_mask & STATX_PTIME) {
+		stat->ptime = ni->i_crtime;
+		stat->result_mask |= STATX_PTIME;
+	}
+
 	stat->blksize = ni->mi.sbi->cluster_size; /* 512, 1K, ..., 2M */
 
 	if (inode->i_flags & S_IMMUTABLE)
@@ -857,6 +864,12 @@ int ntfs_setattr(struct mnt_idmap *idmap, struct dentry *dentry,
 		i_size_write(inode, newsize);
 	}
 
+	/* Accept ptime and store as NTFS creation time */
+	if (ia_valid & ATTR_PTIME) {
+		ni->i_crtime = attr->ia_ptime;
+		ni->ni_flags |= NI_FLAG_UPDATE_PARENT;
+	}
+
 	setattr_copy(idmap, inode, attr);
 
 	if (mode != inode->i_mode) {
diff --git a/fs/ntfs3/frecord.c b/fs/ntfs3/frecord.c
index d5bbd47e1ee9..b164b2f50711 100644
--- a/fs/ntfs3/frecord.c
+++ b/fs/ntfs3/frecord.c
@@ -3197,6 +3197,14 @@ int ni_write_inode(struct inode *inode, int sync, const char *hint)
 			modified = true;
 		}
 
+		/* Write creation time (ptime maps to NTFS cr_time) */
+		ts = ni->i_crtime;
+		dup.cr_time = kernel2nt(&ts);
+		if (std->cr_time != dup.cr_time) {
+			std->cr_time = dup.cr_time;
+			modified = true;
+		}
+
 		dup.fa = ni->std_fa;
 		if (std->fa != dup.fa) {
 			std->fa = dup.fa;
-- 
